related_questions.question: Do I need a travel converter or adapter?
related_questions.snippet: A travel power adapter or European converter adapter fits the plug into the wall socket, while travel converters change the electrical current from 120V to 220V or vice versa. The only time you'll need an international converter is if you're traveling with a device that is not dual voltage.
